==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cycloidei
<hw>Cy*cloi"de*i</hw> <pr>(s?-kloi"d?-?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>ky`klos</grk> circle + <ets>-oid</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An order of fishes, formerly proposed by
Agassiz, for those with thin, smooth scales, destitute of marginal
spines, as the herring and salmon. The group is now regarded as
artificial.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cycloidian</ent>⟦br⟧
